Description: Builds an offline, AI-native reasoning layer on top of the
    'ksTFL' clinical tables framework. Reads the metadata and data JSON
    artefacts produced by 'ksTFL' save_report(), compiles selected outputs
    into a self-contained study registry of table contexts, and provides an
    'ellmer'-backed chat and skill workflow so a medical writer can draft
    clinical study report (CSR) narratives from targeted IDs. Supports
    persisted LLM outputs in markdown/JSON for later reuse and chaining.
    Works with local models via Ollama or LM Studio, or hosted
    OpenAI-compatible providers.
